Mac OS X Public Beta
It was released on September 13, 2000. It costs about $ 29.95. It is the first operating system with a user interface called Aqua. It includes applications such as Preview, Mail, TextEdit, Terminal, and QuickTime Player.

Mac OS X Cheetah (version 10.0)
In fact, this is the first major version of Apple's operating system. It was released on March 24, 2001. The cost is about $ 129. Features include docking station, mail, address book, PDF support, Aqua user interface, Sherlock, secure memory and more.

Mac OS X Puma (version 10.1)
The Mac OS X version was soon named the macOS version. Mac OS X 10.1 Puma was released on September 25, 2001. This is a free update provided to users of its predecessor. It has features like performance enhancement, DVD playback support, advanced menu functions, improved AppleScript, ColorSync, and more.

Mac OS X Jaguar (version 10.2)
Mac OS X is now known as macOS versions. Mac OS X Jaguar Version 10.2 was released on 23 August 2002. It comes as standalone installations or family packages. New features include QuickTime support for MPEG-4. An ink bottle has also been included for handwriting recognition.

Mac OS X Panther (version 10.3, Pinot)
It was released on October 24, 2003. This is Apple's fourth major release of Mac OS X. Its features include Finder, TextEdit, Xcode Developer Tools, QuickTime, Preview, Fast User Switching, and Expose.

Mac OS X Tiger (version 10.4, Merlot)
Mac OS X versions will currently be referred to as macOS versions. Mac OS X Tiger was released on April 29, 2005. Features include Xcode 2.0, QuickTime 7, Mail 2, Dashboard, Spotlight, VoiceOver, iChat AV, and more.

Mac OS X Tiger (version 10.4.4, Chardonnay)
This is an updated version of Mac OS X Tiger 10.4, Merlot. Released 10th January 2006.

Mac OS X Leopard (Version 10.5, Chablis)
Versions of Mac OS X operating systems are now known as macOS versions. This version of the operating system was released on October 26, 2007. New features include a toolbar, parental controls, Photo Booth, Spotlight, Time Machine, universal access, and more.

Mac OS X Snow Leopard (version 10.6)
This is the 7th release of Mac OS X and is now known as macOS versions. It was released on 28 August 2009. Features include Mac App Store, Finder, Boot Camp, Preview, Time Machine, VoiceOver, Safari 4, and more.

Mac OS X Lion (version 10.7, Barolo)
It was released on July 20, 2011. New features include AirDrop, FaceTime, Finder, Font Book 3, Mac App Store, Mail 5, QuickTime, Vertical Text, Resume, and more. Mac OS X is now known as macOS versions.

Mac OS X Mountain Lion (version 10.8, Zinfandel)
Mac OS X versions are now known as macOS versions. It was released on July 25, 2012. Features include Notes, Notification Center, Messages, App Updates, Game Center, and more.

Mac OS X Mavericks (10.9, Cabernet)
It was released on October 22, 2013. System features include iCloud Keychain, Timer Merge, Calendar, iBooks, Maps, Safari Browser, and more. Removed features including Open Transport API.

Mac OS X Yosemite (version 10.10, Syrah)
Mac OS X is now known as macOS versions. Mac OS X Yosemite was released on October 16, 2014. Features include Action Center, Spotlight, Continuity, Better Design, and more.

Mac OS X El Capitan (version 10.11 Holiday)
Mac OS X is now known as macOS versions. It was released on September 20, 2015. Its features include Mail, Messages, Maps, Safari, Notes, Spotlight, and Photos.

macOS Sierra (version 10.12, Fuji)
What will happen after EI Capitan? One of the versions of macOS was released on September 20, 2016. System features include Siri, Night Shift, Universal Clipboard, Auto Unlock, and more. App features include iTunes, Notes, Apple Play, Safari, Photos, and more.

macOS High Sierra (version 10.13, Lobo)
Another version of macOS was released on September 25, 2017. This operating system is focused on providing technical updates and performance improvements, not adding features. The changes include significant improvements to Safari and Photos.

In macOS High Sierra, AFPS (Apple File System) replaces the so-called HFS +. AFPS is now the default file system on macOS. Metal has also been updated to Metal 2. App changes have been made including Final Cut Pro 7, Messages, Siri, Notes, Safari, Mail, Photos, and more.


Tip: If you just want to upgrade your Mac version to High Sierra, you can follow this guide to do so.

macOS Mojave (version 10.14, Liberty)
This is the fifteenth release of the Apple operating system for Mac computers. It was released on September 24, 2018. He added several iOS apps to the operating system
